UML:TaggedValue.value: Application Schema for soil sampling, soil specimens and related observations

ANZSoilML model constraint: At least "nameOfMeasure" and "result" shall be used when delivering om:resultQuality/gmd:DQ_QuantitativeAttributeAccuracy. The characterString in "nameOfMeasure" should be a term from a controlled vocabulary

Soil samples will be treated as SF_SamplingPoints, rather than specific SoilSample features. The geometry of the soil sample should be a 0D point, 1D profile or 2D polygon, not 3D volumes. Therefore the SF_SamplingPoint/parameter property has been used to capture the depth range of the sample rather than being included in the geometry property. Where a 3D geometry is provided the parameter will duplicate the 3D geometry depth.
The XML implementation of the depth range in the SF_SamplingPoint/parameter property will use the ANZSoilML-Core/DepthQuantityRange data type. i.e.: <font color="#800000">anzsml:upperBoundary</font><font color="#ff0000"> </font> <font color="#800000">anzsml:lowerBoundary</font>
A specialisation of SF_Specimen to capture archived specimens. NatSoil archive indicates whether there is a coarse fraction (>2mm) present in the specimen.
Presence or absence of coarse fragment sample >2mm

UML:Comment.name: Description: Unique integer value to order the properties of a class
Values: byReference,inline Default: inline Description: Determines whether the property value will be encoded inline or by reference
Values: true,false Default: false Description: If 'true', the property type will extend GML AbstractMetadataPropertyType. Else, it will extend GML AbstractMemberType.

UML:TaggedValue.value: A specialisation of SF_SpatialSamplingFeature for soil sampling features.
Use the OM_Observation/resultQuality/ DQ_QuantitativeAttributeAccuracy attribute to represent analytical errors and detection limits for each analytical measurement.
Use relatedSamplingFeature/ SamplingFeatureComplex/role to specify 'archived specimen' and 'source sample'
